#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1229
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can add new terminals to the drop-down menu by using the green plus sign next to it."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1235
#, no-c-format
msgid "Manually Providing the Phonetic Transcription"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1236
#, no-c-format
msgid "The pronunciation is a bit trickier. simon does not need a certain type of phonetics so you are free to use any method as long as it uses only ASCII characters and no numbers. However, if you want to use a shadow dictionary and want to use it to it's full potential you should use the same phonetics as the shadow dictionary."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1240
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you don't know how to transcribe a word yourself you can easily use your shadow dictionary to help you with the transcription - even if the word is not listed in it. Let's say we want to add the word \"Firefox\" (to launch firefox) which is of course not listed in our shadow dictionary."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1244
#, no-c-format
msgid "(I imported the English voxforge HTK lexicon available from <ulink url=\"http://voxforge.org/home/downloads\">voxforge</ulink> as a shadow dictionary.)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1248
#, no-c-format
msgid "\"Firefox\" is not listed in our shadow dictionary so we don't get any suggestion at all."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:1251
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding an unknown word"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1260
#, no-c-format
msgid "However, we know that firefox sounds like \"fire\" and \"fox\" put together. So let's just open the vocabulary (you can keep the wizard open) by selecting \"Vocabulary\" from your simon main toolbar."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1263
#, no-c-format
msgid "Switch to the shadow vocabulary by clicking on the tab <guilabel>Shadow Vocabulary</guilabel>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1265
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use the \"Filter\"-Box above the list to search for \"Fire\":"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:1269
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding an unknown word: Search for the Pronunciation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1278
#, no-c-format
msgid "We can see, that the word \"Fire\" is transcribed as \"f ay r\". Now filter for \"fox\" instead of \"Fire\" and we can see that \"Fox\" is transcribed as \"f ao k s\". We can assume, that firefox should be transcribed as \"f ay r f ao k s\"."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1282
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using this approach of deducing the pronunciation from parts of the word has the distinct advantage that we not only get a high quality transcription but also automatically use the same phoneme set as the other words which were correctly pulled out of the shadow dictionary."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1286
#, no-c-format
msgid "We can now enter the pronunciation and change the terminal to something appropriate."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:1289
#, no-c-format
msgid "Completely defined word"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1303
#, no-c-format
msgid "Training the Word"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1304
#, no-c-format
msgid "To complete the wizard we can now train the word twice. If you don't want to do this or for example use a <link linkend=\"base_model_static\">static base model</link>, you can skip these two pages."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1309
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you are using static or adapted base models, you can of course skip this step."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1314
#, no-c-format
msgid "Because you are about to record some training samples, simon will display the volume calibration to make sure that your microphone is set up correctly. For more information please refer to the <link linkend=\"volume_calibration\">volume calibration section</link>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1318
#, no-c-format
msgid "simon will try to prompt you for real-world examples. To do that, simon will automatically fetch grammar structures using the terminal of the word and substitute the generic terminals with example words from your active lexicon."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1321
#, no-c-format
msgid "For example: You have the grammar structure \"Trigger Command\" and have the word \"Computer\" of the terminal \"Trigger\" in your vocabulary. You then add a new word \"Firefox\" of the terminal \"Command\". simon will now automatically prompt you for \"Computer Firefox\" as it is - according to your grammar - a valid sentence."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1324
#, no-c-format
msgid "If simon is unable to find appropriate sentences using the word (i.e.: No grammar, not enough words in your active lexicon, etc.) it will just prompt you for the word alone."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1327
#, no-c-format
msgid "Although simon ensures that the automatically generated examples are valid, you can always override it's suggestion. Just switch to the \"Examples\" tab on the \"Define Word\" page."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:1330
#, no-c-format
msgid "Editing word examples"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1339
#, no-c-format
msgid "You are free to change those examples to anything you like. You can even go so far and use words that are not yet in your active lexicon as long as you add them before you synchronize the model, although this is not recommended."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1343
#, no-c-format
msgid "All that is left is to record the examples."
